HEADWORD: Primipilar
<hw>Pri*mip"i*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>primipilaris</ets>, fr. <ets>primipilus</ets> the centurion of the
first cohort of a Roman legion, fr. <ets>primus pilus</ets> the division
made up of the triarii in the Roman army.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining
to the captain of the vanguard of a Roman army.</def>
